'''''HoloNet News Vol. 531'' #54''' was one of many [[in-universe]] [[HoloNet News (original website)|HoloNet News]] issues published shortly before the release of [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']]. This issue was released [[May 2]], [[2002]].

{{Media-stub}}

==Contents==
*'''NEWS''':
**[[Dooku/Legends|Dooku]] Spotted in Gree Enclave
**Rodian [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] Uncovers Loyalist-Separatist Ties
**Senator Taa Apologizes Over Dod "Joke"

*'''BUSINESS''':
**Cease & Desist turns into Seek & Destroy

*'''REGIONAL''':
**Yag'Dhul Secedes
**Hunger Pangs Start to Hit The Colonies
**Malastare to Increase Import Security
**Vigilante Task Force Departs to Engage [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatists]]

*'''JEDI WATCH''':
**[[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] Settle Ansion Dispute
**Corellian Jedi Return

*'''SPORTS''':
**Ominaz Keeps Top Ranking

*'''LIFE''':
**Study Warns of Impending Parking Extinction
**Giant Space Slug Found

*'''Other headlines:'''
**Palpatine: A Complete Biography See REPUBLIC D 12
**Gun Control: Who Are We Kidding? See EDITORIAL G 12
**Corrections See APPENDIX Y 3-24

==Continuity==
This issue contains the first canonical image of [[Selkath/Legends|Selkath]] in the "Dooku Spotted in the Gree Enclave" article.

